---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'AXA Global Review', href: '/providers/axa-global' },
  { title: 'Best Budget Expat Insurance', href: '/best/budget-expat-insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', img: true, axa: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', img: true, axa: true },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', img: 'Limited', axa: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', img: '12 mo wait', axa: '10-12 mo wait' },
  { feature: 'Dental', img: 'Optional', axa: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Telemedicine', img: true, axa: true },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', img: true, axa: true },
  { feature: 'US Coverage', img: 'Included (most plans)', axa: 'Add-on' },
  { feature: 'Max Deductible', img: '$25,000', axa: '€5,000' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'age', header: 'Age' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { age: '30', img: '$120-200/mo', axa: '$140-220/mo' },
  { age: '40', img: '$160-280/mo', axa: '$190-300/mo' },
  { age: '50', img: '$220-360/mo', axa: '$260-400/mo' },
  { age: '60', img: '$340-520/mo', axa: '$380-580/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="IMG Global vs AXA Global"
  description="Compare IMG Global and AXA Global health insurance. US-based flexibility vs European established insurer for expats."
  headline="IMG Global vs AXA Global"
  subheadline="Value-tier comparison: US flexibility vs European establishment."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
    <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global and AXA Global are both popular choices for international health insurance, but they serve different needs. Understanding their key differences will help you choose the right coverage for your situation abroad.
  </p>
  <p>
    IMG Global is offering affordable international health insurance with flexible options. Their main budget-friendly plans that still provide solid coverage. They're particularly popular among budget-conscious expats and digital nomads, with lower premiums with higher deductible options available.
  </p>
  <p>
    AXA Global is part of the French AXA group, offering robust international health plans. They're known for their strong presence in Europe and Asia with comprehensive plan options. They tend to attract expats in Europe and Asia who want a well-established provider, offering competitive pricing with flexible deductible options.
  </p>
  <p>
    This comparison breaks down the key differences between these two providers so you can make an informed decision. We'll cover coverage options, pricing estimates, network access, claims processes, and help you determine which one makes more sense for your specific needs and budget.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">IMG Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>US-based insurer</li>
        <li>Highly customizable plans</li>
        <li>Very high deductible options</li>
        <li>US coverage included by default</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">AXA Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>French-headquartered global insurer</li>
        <li>Strong financial backing</li>
        <li>Good European network</li>
        <li>Modular plan structure</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Value Options"
    description="Get quotes from both value-tier insurers."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    Both offer solid international coverage. Key differences are in US coverage approach and deductible flexibility.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p><strong>Key differences:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>IMG includes US coverage by default; AXA charges extra</li>
    <li>IMG offers much higher deductible options for premium savings</li>
    <li>AXA has stronger European network presence</li>
    <li>Both have similar (limited) mental health coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    IMG is typically 10-15% cheaper, and the gap widens with high-deductible strategies. AXA may be comparable when US coverage isn't needed.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p><strong>Pricing notes:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>IMG prices include US coverage</li>
    <li>AXA prices exclude US (add 30-40% for inclusion)</li>
    <li>IMG's $25K deductible option can cut premiums 40%+</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global</strong> has good worldwide coverage with moderate direct billing availability.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>AXA Global</strong> has particularly strong networks in Europe and parts of Asia, reflecting its French headquarters.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    Both offer online claims submission. AXA's processes may feel more familiar to European expats. IMG's system is straightforward but US-oriented.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose IMG Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You need US coverage</li>
        <li>You want high-deductible options</li>
        <li>Maximum customization matters</li>
        <li>You're American or US-based</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose AXA Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You don't need US coverage</li>
        <li>You're based in Europe</li>
        <li>You prefer European service style</li>
        <li>Financial strength is a priority</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    For Americans or anyone needing US coverage, IMG Global offers better value with more flexibility. The high-deductible options are particularly attractive for healthy individuals wanting catastrophic coverage.
  </p>
  <p>
    For Europeans or those who don't need US coverage, AXA Global is competitive and offers the backing of one of the world's largest insurers. The European network strength is a real advantage for those based in the EU.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Get quotes from both providers."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Prices and coverage details change. Verify all information with providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
